OL,3,CMother of son who was killed in the
OL,4,CNottingham attacks speaks of her grief
OL,6,FSaid said: "If it helps other people
OL,7,Fto know that it's ok, that other
OL,8,Fpeople are going through stuff too,
OL,9,Fand it's ok to reach out. It's ok to
OL,10,Fhave terrible days. It's ok to have
OL,11,Fthose duvet days, then I'm really
OL,12,Fhonoured to do that."
OL,14,FLast year, on the 1st anniversary of
OL,15,Fthe attacks, 100s of people gathered
OL,16,Fat Nottingham University where Barnaby
OL,17,Fand Grace were students for a special
OL,18,Fmemorial service.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/12
